An Entish fountain that grows Entwood, useful in Ent-craft and brewing.
Rune-cooled shelves for meal ingredients. Stores a Cook’s herbs, meat, and mountain fare. Cooks will only use crafting ingredients placed in this container.
Iron-bound bin piled with raw ore and fuel. Feeds the Furnace for the Metalworker’s hand. Metalworkers will only use crafting ingredients placed in this container.
Heavy sack of barley, oats and spices. A Brewmaster’s store for the ale to come. Brewmasters will only use crafting ingredients placed in this container.
A small structure marking a key point to keep watch from. Guards will stand watch here if nearby.
A carved relief of the Misty Mountains used to plan expeditions for resources.
A traditional Dwarven claim marker. Set near rich rock seams to designate where the Company should work. Miners will only work on veins near this.
A stout wooden keg that can filled by a Brewmaster. Holds fresh ale for the Delving. Any Dwarf at merrymaking may draw a hearty mug.
A more-or-less organized pile of items the Delving no longer needs. A Tinker will spend time breaking items into their raw materials. Any contents can be permanently destroyed by the player.

A massive geode split open to reveal crystalline beauty within, displaying the vast natural wealth of Moria. Building this will spread word of the abundance to be had here and will unlock the Trading Camp outside the Westgate.
A metal spire of Dashun, or pride, houses an eternal vertical flame that burns without fuel or tending.

A towering cylinder carved with the likenesses of the Unukh-âhîn, the Seven Fathers of the Dwarven clans. Modelled after a long ruined second-age monument in Dwarrowdelf, completing this sends word that the Company is here to stay.
A hollow pillar containing Umrad-ukhfur, scrolls and books of forgotten lore.
An impregnable vault built to contain that which must never see light. This khafrûn-unshi, or sealed evil, is dangerous to wield, yet too precious to destroy.
A sturdy wooden stand built for the great raven Aric. Building this perch welcomes the wise corvid to roost and share his sage counsel with the Company.
Meal table with seats that allow Dwarves to sit and enjoy their meal.

This crystal beacon crowns Zirak-zigil, its light visible across all Middle-earth. As its name, Tahbûn, infers it is a rallying call to all scattered Dwarves that Moria welcomes them home. Restoring the Beacon unlocks the Recruiting Camp outside the Dimrill Gate.

A ring of stone circles surrounding a central pedestal. Its use is unknown but resembles crude oath circles used in Dwarven family inheritance and marriage rituals. There is no greater place to cement an oath than on this peak.
A stout frame stacked with forged metal bars. Holds the Blacksmith’s stock close to the Forge. Blacksmiths will only use crafting ingredients placed in this container.
A rune-locked chest for gems, wires, and gold. Keeps an Artisan’s finest craft safe from theft or fire. Artisans will only use crafting ingredients placed in this container.
Wooden hutch with shelves for cloth bolts. Keeps a Tailor’s wool, linen, and silk dry and ready. Tailors will only use crafting ingredients placed in this container.
A large storage chest designated as the only place company Dwarves and crafters will automatically deposit their inventories.
An Elven style Mansion Bed. Sleep here to recover energy and feel well rested.
An impressive chest in a Noldorian style. When near a hearth, all crafting can use the contents without them being removed.
